definition.value: A chemical entity is a material entity that pertains to chemistry.
A gene is part of a nucleic acid that contains all the necessary elements to encode a functional transcript.
a protein is an organic polymer that is composed of one or more linear polymers of amino acids.
a biological entity is a heterogeneous substance that contains genomic material or is the product of a biological process.
an amino acid residue is a part of a molecule that is derived from an amino acid molecule.
A submolecule is a mereological sum of a collection of covalently bonded atoms.
A molecule is the mereological maximal sum of a collection of covalently bonded atoms.
